Process called "get_file_extension" takes file_path as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract file extension from path

    @Reasoning:
    Extension extraction must work the same way on POSIX and Windows
    paths because the translation driver runs on every platform Runa
    supports. The substring is returned as a freshly allocated,
    null-terminated buffer so the caller owns the lifetime and is
    free to retain or discard it independent of the source path.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation:
    Walk the path byte-by-byte from the tail toward the head looking
    for the last '.'. If a path separator ('/' on POSIX, '\' on
    Windows) is hit before the dot, the file has no extension and 0
    is returned. When a dot is found, allocate ext_length+1 bytes,
    memcpy the suffix, and write a trailing NUL. Returns the buffer
    address or 0 on allocation failure / no extension / null input.
    @End Implementation

    @Security_Scope:
    Bounds-safe: i runs strictly in [0, path_length) so memory_get_byte
    never reads past the buffer. Allocation failure is propagated, not
    silently masked, so the caller can detect and recover.
    @End Security_Scope

    If file_path is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let path_length be proc string_length from StringCore with file_path
    Let i be path_length minus 1

    Note: Search backwards for dot
    While i is greater than or equal to 0:
        Let char be proc memory_get_byte from Layout with file_path, i

        If char is equal to 46:  Note: '.' character
            Note: Found dot - extract extension
            Let ext_start be i
            Let ext_length be path_length minus ext_start
            Let extension be proc allocate from Layout with ext_length plus 1

            If extension is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If

            Note: Copy extension
            proc memory_copy from Layout with extension, 0, file_path, ext_start, ext_length
            proc memory_set_byte from Layout with extension, ext_length, 0  Note: Null terminate

            Return extension
        End If

        If char is equal to 47:  Note: '/' character (path separator)
            Return 0  Note: No extension found
        End If

        If char is equal to 92:  Note: '\' character (Windows path separator)
            Return 0  Note: No extension found
        End If

        Set i to i minus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "get_language_name" takes language_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get human-readable language name from constant

    @Reasoning:
    Diagnostic output, log lines, and metadata payloads need a
    canonical display name for every supported language. Keeping the
    name table inside translation.runa rather than in each backend
    means the orchestrator can emit cross-language error messages
    without round-tripping into the language-specific emitters.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation:
    Direct LANG_* constant switch returning interned string literals.
    Cases are grouped to match the constant declaration order
    (C-family, modern statically typed, dynamic, JVM, functional,
    scientific, blockchain, frontend frameworks, assembly/IR, HDL,
    shell, data formats, markup, query, build) for easy maintenance
    when a new language is added. Falls through to "Unknown" so
    diagnostics never produce a blank slot.
    @End Implementation

    Note: Runa
    If language_id is equal to LANG_RUNA:
        Return "Runa"
    End If

    Note: C-family languages
    If language_id is equal to LANG_C:
        Return "C"
    End If
    If language_id is equal to LANG_CPP:
        Return "C++"
    End If
    If language_id is equal to LANG_CSHARP:
        Return "C#"
    End If
    If language_id is equal to LANG_COBOL:
        Return "COBOL"
    End If

