Note: ============================================================================
Note: Language Feature Detection
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "get_language_features" takes language_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get feature flags for specified language

    @Reasoning:
    Returns bitflags indicating language features for semantic mapping.
    Different languages have different type systems, memory models, and
    concurrency primitives, so the translator must know what features
    are available in each target before lowering. This table is the
    single source of truth used by check_translation_compatibility,
    estimate_translation_accuracy, and per-backend feature gating in
    translation/backends/* so a feature added here propagates to
    every consumer automatically.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation:
    Accumulate FEAT_* constants into an Integer bitset using a switch
    on language_id. Each language adds the flags it natively supports
    across five axes: type-system discipline (FEAT_STATIC_TYPING /
    DYNAMIC / STRONG / WEAK / TYPE_INFERENCE), memory management
    (MANUAL / GC / OWNERSHIP / REFCOUNT), paradigm (OBJECT_ORIENTED /
    FUNCTIONAL / PROCEDURAL / DECLARATIVE), and concurrency (THREADS /
    ASYNC_AWAIT / CHANNELS / GOROUTINES). Languages outside the
    programming-language set (HDL, markup, data formats) return 0.
    @End Implementation

    Let features be 0

    Note: Runa language features (all features)
    If language_id is equal to LANG_RUNA:
        Set features to features plus FEAT_STATIC_TYPING
        Set features to features plus FEAT_STRONG_TYPING
