Process called "is_language_supported" takes language_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if language is supported by Translation

    @Reasoning:
    The driver and IDE integrations need to enumerate supported
    languages so they can populate completion menus, validate
    user-facing options, and reject obvious misconfigurations
    before any I/O happens. Centralizing the language-support set
    in this single predicate ensures all consumers agree on which
    LANG_* constants currently have working backends.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation:
    Direct switch on language_id returning 1 for every supported
    LANG_* constant. Languages are grouped to mirror the constant
    declarations and the get_language_name switch, so adding a
    new language requires updating all three locations in lock
    step. Returns 0 for unknown / sentinel values like
    LANG_UNKNOWN.
    @End Implementation

    Note: Runa is native and always supported
    If language_id is equal to LANG_RUNA:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Core languages (fully implemented)
    If language_id is equal to LANG_C:
        Return 1
    End If

