Process called "get_translation_version" returns Integer:
    Note: Get Translation infrastructure version

    @Reasoning:
    Diagnostic helper that lets the driver and IDE integrations
    report which translation-system revision generated a piece of
    output. Versioning the orchestrator separately from the
    compiler as a whole lets consumers detect when translation
    behavior may have changed between two otherwise identical
    runa binaries.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation:
    Returns a string literal encoding the major.minor.patch of the
    universal translation system plus a -complete suffix marking
    that all 52 backends are wired into the dispatcher. The value
    is updated by hand whenever the supported-language set or the
    public translate_to_hir / translate_from_hir contract changes.
    @End Implementation

    Note: v0.0.8.5: Complete universal translation system
    Note: 52 languages with full HIR bidirectional translation support
    Return "0.0.8.5-complete"
End Process

Note: End of Translation infrastructure implementation
Note: Universal translation system supporting 52 languages with complete HIR integration
